==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unclasp
<hw>Un*clasp"</hw> <pr>(⟦ucr⟧n*kl⟦adot⟧sp")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<ety>[1st pref. <ets>un-</ets> + <ets>clasp</ets>.]</ety> <def>To loose
the clasp of; to open, as something that is fastened with, or as with, a
clasp; <as>as, to <ex>unclasp</ex> a book; to <ex>unclasp</ex> the
hands; to <ex>unclasp</ex> one's heart</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uncle</ent>⟦br⟧
